erator|Consolidated PB4Y Liberattor]] aircraft of [[United States Navy]] squadron VB-108. Lost with all 107 hands.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Narita Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk in the Pacific Ocean off [[Hollandia, New Guinea]] by [[Douglas A-26 Invader]], [[Consolidated B-24 Liberator]], [[North American B-25 Mitchell]] and [[Martin B-26 Marauder]] aircraft of the United States [[Fifth Air Force]].<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|PT-135}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass2-|ELCO 80'|PT boat}} was scuttled after running aground north of Crater Point, New Britain ({{coord|05|21|S|152|09|E}}).<ref>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/10179.html |title=PT 135 of the US Navy |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=12 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese landing ship|SS 6||2}} and {{ship|Japanese landing ship|SS 9||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass2-|SS|landing ship}}s were sunk by US aircraft near [[Mindoro]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/japan/jap_aux_ss.htm |title=SS Type Landing Ships of WW II, Japan |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=27 July 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|StuBo 1045||2}}    \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The StuBo42 type landing craft/motor launch was sunk on this date.<ref name=\"navypedia.org\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Taichu Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[cargo liner]] was torpedoed and sunk in the Pacific Ocean east of [[Okinawa]], Japan ({{coord|08|08|N|128|57|E}}) by {{USS|Halibut|SS-232|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=Halibut>{{cite DANFS | title = Halibut | url = http://www.hazegray.org/danfs/submar/ss232.txt | accessdate = 1 January 2012 }}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==13 April==