bay]], [[British Raj|India]].<ref name=\"Ships lost in the Bombay explosion\">{{cite web |url=http://merchantships.tripod.com/fortcreviershipslost.html |title=Ships lost in the Bombay explosion |publisher=tripod |accessdate=14 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMHS|Chantilly|63|6}}\n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Bombay Explosion (1944)|Bombay Explosion]]: The [[hospital ship]] was severely damaged by the explosion of ''Fort Stikine'' ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}) at [[Bombay]], [[British Raj|India]]. She was subsequently repaired and returned to service.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMIS|El Hind}} \n|flag={{navy|British India}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Bombay Explosion (1944)|Bombay Explosion]]: The [[Landing ship infantry|landing ship infantry (large)]] was burned out as a result of the explosion of ''Fort Stikine'' ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}) at [[Bombay]], [[British India|India]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/13447.html |title=Landing Ship Infantry HMIS El Hind |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=14 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Fort Crevier||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Bombay Explosion (1944)|Bombay Explosion]]: The [[Fort ship]] was severely damaged by the explosion of ''Fort Stikine'' ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}) at [[Bombay]], [[British India|India]]. She was subsequently used as a [[hulk (ship)|hulk]] until scrapped in 1948. A crewman was killed.<ref name=FortAJ>{{cite web |url=http://www.mariners-l.co.uk/FortA.html |title=Fort Ships A-J |publisher=Mariners |accessdate=5 January 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Fort Stikine||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Bombay Explosion (1944)|Bombay Explosion]]: The [[Fort ship]] exploded and sank at Bombay. The explosion resulted in the loss of many more ships.<ref name=FortKS>{{cite web |url=http://www.mariners-l.co.uk