any}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[naval trawler]] was bombed and sunk in the [[Barents Sea]] off [[Makkaur]], Norway by [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Sumida Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship struck a [[naval mine|mine]] and sank in the [[Pacific Ocean]] off [[Honshu]].<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German submarine chaser|UJ 2141||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[submarine chaser]] was bombed and sunk in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] by British aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=[[Japanese minesweeper No. 7 (1938)|''W-7'']] \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass2-|No.7|minesweeper|||1938}} was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Indian Ocean]] off the [[Nicobar Islands]] ({{coord|11|34|N|93|08|E}}) by {{HMS|Storm|P233|6}} ({{navy|United Kingdom}}).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/W-12_t.htm |title=Japanese Minesweepers |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=15 April 2013}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==16 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=16 April 1944 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|AF 1|F 288|2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The Type A ''[[Artillerief\u00e4hrprahm]]'' was bombed and sunk at [[Boulogne-sur-Mer|Boulogne]], [[Pas-de-Calais]], France by Allied aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German lighter|Dordogne||2}}  \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The lighter was sunk by a mine in the [[Black Sea]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soviet-empire.com/ussr/viewtopic.php?f=149&t=55255&sid=b64d81afc6dc3bf6ebf262ded5ddeaf9 |title=Soviet torpedo bomber victories during WWII |publisher=Sovietempire.com |accessdate=7 April 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Germa