y.org/danfs/submar/ss257.txt | accessdate = 3 January 2012 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese minesweeper|Noshiro Maru No. 2||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The auxiliary minesweeper was torpedoed and sunk in the Pacific Ocean by {{USS|Searaven|SS-196|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-342||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC]] [[submarine]] was depth charged and sunk in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] ({{coord|60|32|N|29|20|W}}) by a [[Consolidated PBY Catalina]] aircraft of [[No. 162 Squadron RCAF|162 Squadron]], [[Royal Canadian Air Force]] with the loss of all 51 crew.<ref name=U342>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/boats/u342.htm |title=U-342 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=16 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-986||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC]] [[submarine]] was depth charged and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean south west of Iceland ({{Coord|50|09|N|12|51|W}}) by {{USS|PC-619}} and {{USS|Swift|AM-122|6}} (both {{navy|USA|1912}}) with the loss of all 50 crew.<ref name=U986>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/boats/u986.htm |title=U-986 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==18 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=18 April 1944 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet landing boat|DB-35||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=The No. 1-class landing boat was lost on this date.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/russia/ru_ls_db.htm |title=No. 1 class landing boat, USSR |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=27 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet submarine|L-6||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The {{sclass-|Leninets|submarine|2}} was sunk in the [[Black Sea]] east of [[Constanta, Romania]] ({{coord|43|