rt Townsend, Washington|Port Townsend]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]], to [[Dutch Harbor, Alaska|Dutch Harbor]], [[Territory of Alaska]], with a cargo of highly flammable cargo of fuel, the [[Liberty ship]], operating as a [[cargo ship]] for the [[United States Army]] was [[torpedo]]ed by {{ship|Japanese submarine|I-180||2}} ({{navy|Empire of Japan}}) and broke in two in the [[Pacific Ocean]] at {{coord|54|22|N|163|24|W|name=SS ''John Straub''}}, approximately {{convert|20|nmi}} southeast of [[Sanak Island]] in the [[Fox Islands (Alaska)|Fox Islands]] subgroup of the [[Aleutian Islands]].  The [[Bow (ship)|bow]] section sank. The [[stern]] section was [[Scuttling|scuttled]] by the [[patrol frigate]] {{USS|Albuquerque|PF-7|6}} ({{navy|United States|1912}}). A passenger, 14 embarked personnel of the [[United States Navy Armed Guard]], and 40 crewmen were killed. Her 15 survivors were rescued by the cargo ship ''FP 41'' ({{army|United States|1912}}).<ref name=alaskashipwrecksj>[https://alaskashipwreck.com/shipwrecks-a-z/alaska-shipwrecks-j/ alaskashipwreck.com Alaska Shipwrecks (J)]</ref><ref name=LibJo>{{cite web |url=http://www.mariners-l.co.uk/LibShipsJo.html |title=Liberty Ships \u2013 Joaquin \u2013 Johns |publisher=Mariners |accessdate=6 January 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/I-180.htm |title=Imperial submarines |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=18 April 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Jos\u00e9 Illucea||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Spain|1938}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[coastal trading vessel|coaster]] was bombed and sunk in the [[Gulf of Lyon]] by [[Bristol Beaufighter]] aircraft of [[Royal Air Force]]. Two crew were killed.<ref name=seekrieg194404/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://calm3.jimdo.com/app/download/6251590151/operationsgolfelionc-a-l-m-3.pdf?t=1488280582 |title=Jos\u00e9 Illucea |publisher=calm3.jimdo.com |accessdate=19 April 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|ST|Kampung Besar||2}}