andoned by her 51 crew. They were rescued by {{SS|Goodwin||2}} ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}). ''Oldham'' was towed to [[St. John's, Newfoundland and Labrador|St. John's]], [[Dominion of Newfoundland|Newfoundland]].<ref name=SC156W>{{cite web |url=http://www.warsailors.com/convoys/sc156.html |title=Convoy SC.156 |publisher=Warsailors |accessdate=24 May 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|Sperrbrecher 193 Albrecht Durer||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The river ''[[Sperrbrecher]]'' was bombed by Soviet aircraft in the Black Sea and had to be run aground north of [[Sulina]]. She was then abandonned.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_conc_rmdv.htm |title=River mine destruction vessels of WWII, Converted Merchant ships, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=22 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://opus4.kobv.de/opus4-zmsbw/frontdoor/index/index/searchtype/series/id/1/rows/10/start/20/docId/69 |title=Kriegstagebuch der Seekriegsleitung 1939 - 1945. - Teil A ; Band 56. April 1944 |publisher=opus4.kobv.de |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://blackseavisits.ru/korabli/1941-1945/en/KM_Sp-193%20%20Sperrbrecher-193.html |title=Sperrbrecher 193 |publisher=blackseavisits.ru |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet motor torpedo boat|TKA-212||2}}  \n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=World War II: The A-2 (Higgins 78')-class motor torpedo boat was shelled and sunk by {{ship|German submarine chaser|UJ-1219||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) in the [[Barents Sea]] during an attack on a German convoy. Two crewmen were made [[prisoners of war]] and 11 were killed.<ref name=seekrieg194404/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/russia/ru_cf_a2.htm |title=A-2 class motor torpedo boat, USSR |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=27 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soviet-empire.com/ussr/viewtopic.php?f=149&t=53532&sid=6447e85e3ab126d0f28fae62df794abf |title=Soviet Naval Battles-Arctic Sea |publisher=Sovietempire.com |accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://forum.vgd.ru/post/585/55474/p1673806.htm |title=TKA-212 |publisher=forum.vgd.ru |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-68|1940|2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type IX submarine|Type IXC]] [[submarine]] was sunk in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] ({{coord|33|24|N|18|59|W}}) by [[Grumman TBF Avenger]] and [[Grumman F4F Wildcat]] aircraft based on {{USS|Guadalcanal|CVE-60|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}) with the loss of 56 of her 57 crew. }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==11 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=11 April 1944 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|AF 24|F 270|2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The Type A ''[[Artillerief\u00e4hrprahm]]'' was sunk at [[Stettin]], [[Province of Pomerania (1815-1945)|Pomerania]] during an American air raid.<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese destroyer|Akigumo|1941|2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Kager\u014d|destroyer|2}} was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Moro Gulf]] {{convert|30|nmi|km}} south east of Zamboanga ({{coord|6|43|N|122|23|E}}) by {{USS|Redfin|SS-272|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}). One hundred and thirty-seven people were killed, including her commanding officer.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Emily|1882|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Denmark}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was sunk at Stettin during an American air raid.<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 300||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The Type B ''[[Marinef\u00e4hrprahm]]'' was sunk at Stettin during an American air raid.<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 389||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The ''Marinef\u00e4hrprahm'' was sunk at Stettin during an American air raid.<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|Holder|DE-401|6}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The {{sclass-|Edsall|destroyer escort|2}} was [[torpedo]]ed and damaged in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] off [[Algiers]], [[French Algeria|Algeria]] by [[Luftwaffe]] aircraft. Her crew lost 17 killed and 12 wounded. She was towed to [[Oran]] and then to [[New York City|New York]], where she was condemned. A {{convert|95|ft|m|adj=on}} section of her stern was used to repair {{USS|Menges|DE-320|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ussholder.com/DE401-Too-Short-A-Time-P2.html |title=USS Holder |publisher=www.ussholder.com |accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|M 6022 Enseigne||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[minesweeper]] was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] ({{coord|43|22|N|07|00|E}}) by {{HMS|Untiring|P59|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German training ship|Mars||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[artillery]] [[training ship]] was bombed and destroyed by fire at [[Stettin]] in an American air raid.<ref name=seekrieg194404/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deutschekriegsmarine.de/hauptteil_uberwassereinheiten/hauptteil_sonderschiffe/hauptteil_schulschiffe/hauptteil_artillerieschulschif/hauptteil_artillerieschulschiffe.htm |title=Artillerieschulschiffe |publisher=www.deutschekriegsmarine.de  \u2013  Die deutsche Kriegsmarine von 1939 |accessdate=2 March 2012 |language=German}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|R-27||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[R boat|Type R-25 minesweeper]] was sunk in the Pilava-Konigsberg Canal by [[naval mine|mines]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=761 |title=German coastal minesweeper Type R-25 |publisher=Warshipsww2.Eu |accessdate=2 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006194034/http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=761 |archive-date=6 October 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|R-204||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[R boat|Type R-151 minesweeper]] was sunk by Soviet aircraft at [[Feodosija]], [[Soviet Union]]. Raised, repaired, and put into [[Soviet Navy]] service as ''BO-51''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=764 |title=German coastal minesweeper Type R-151 |publisher=Warshipsww2.Eu |accessdate=25 November 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140513030230/http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=764 |archive-date=13 May 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=1825 |title=Soviet Union Small Submarine Chasers Ex-German |publisher=Warshipsww2.Eu |accessdate=25 November 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141201235147/http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=1825 |archive-date=1 December 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|St\u00f6r|1921|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Barents Sea]] off [[Kirkenes]], Norway.<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=5605497|shipname=Stor |accessdate=15 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-108|1940|2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type IX submarine|Type IXB]] [[submarine]] was bombed and sunk at Stettin in an American air raid. She was raised on 17 July and decommissioned. Scuttled on 24 April 1945.<ref name=seekrieg194404/><ref name=U108>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/boats/u108.htm |title=U-108 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=23 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-902||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC]] [[submarine]] was sunk at Stettin during an American air raid.<ref name=seekrieg194404/> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German submarine chaser|UJ 2143 Aghios Trias||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The auxiliary submarine chaser was lost on this date.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_conc_patrol.htm |title=Auxiliary Guard ships and Minesweepers of WWII, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=18 April 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==12 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=12 April 1944 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|ATR-98}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=The rescue [[tugboat]] was sunk in a collision with the tugboat {{USS|Abnaki|ATF-96|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}) off [[The Azores]] ({{coord|44|04|N|24|08|W}}).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ibiblio.org/hyperwar/USN/USN-Chron/USN-Chron-1944.html |title=Official Cronology of the US Navy in WWII |publisher=Ibiblio |accessdate=12 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Cerere||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The [[tank ship|tanker]] was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] by {{HMS|Untiring|P59|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Diana|Bremer Vulkan, 1901|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the Mediterranean Sea ({{coord|43|25|N|06|51|E}}) south of [[Oneglia]], Italy by {{HMS|Untiring|P59|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{Jsub|I-174||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Kaidai|submarine|2}} was [[depth charge]]d and sunk in the [[Pacific Ocean]] east of [[Chuuk Lagoon|Truk]], [[South Pacific Mandate]] ({{coord|10|05|N|152|29|E}}) by a [[Consolidated B-24 Liberator|Consolidated PB4Y Liberattor]] aircraft of [[United States Navy]] squadron VB-108. Lost with all 107 hands.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Narita Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk in the Pacific Ocean off [[Hollandia, New Guinea]] by [[Douglas A-26 Invader]], [[Consolidated B-24 Liberator]], [[North American B-25 Mitchell]] and [[Martin B-26 Marauder]] aircraft of the United States [[Fifth Air Force]].<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|PT-135}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass2-|ELCO 80'|PT boat}} was scuttled after running aground north of Crater Point, New Britain ({{coord|05|21|S|152|09|E}}).<ref>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/10179.html |title=PT 135 of the US Navy |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=12 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese landing ship|SS 6||2}} and {{ship|Japanese landing ship|SS 9||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass2-|SS|landing ship}}s were sunk by US aircraft near [[Mindoro]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/japan/jap_aux_ss.htm |title=SS Type Landing Ships of WW II, Japan |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=27 July 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|StuBo 1045||2}}    \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The StuBo42 type landing craft/motor launch was sunk on this date.<ref name=\"navypedia.org\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Taichu Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[cargo liner]] was torpedoed and sunk in the Pacific Ocean east of [[Okinawa]], Japan ({{coord|08|08|N|128|57|E}}) by {{USS|Halibut|SS-232|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=Halibut>{{cite DANFS | title = Halibut | url = http://www.hazegray.org/danfs/submar/ss232.txt | accessdate = 1 January 2012 }}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==13 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=13 April 1944 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 565||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The Type C2 ''[[Marinef\u00e4hrprahm]]'' was sunk in the Black Sea by Soviet aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194404/><ref name=\"MFP landing craft, Germany\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese destroyer|Ikazuchi|1931|2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Fubuki|destroyer|2}} was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in the [[Pacific Ocean]] {{convert|200|nmi|km}} south south east of Guam ({{coord|10|13|N|143|51|E}}) by {{USS|Harder|SS-257|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}). Lost with all hands.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Solvoll'' \n|flag={{flag|Norway}}\n|desc=World War II: The fishing vessel was shelled and sunk in the [[Norwegian Sea]] {{convert|150|nmi|km}} west of the [[Lofoten Islands]] by {{GS|U-711||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}). All eight people on board were taken on board ''U-711'' as prisoners and were held by the [[Gestapo]] until the end of the war.<ref name=Solvoll>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1756.html |title=Solvoll |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=17 April 2012}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==14 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=14 April 1944 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|B\u00e4renfels|1921|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The cargo ship struck [[naval mine|mines]] and sank in the [[Norwegian Sea]] off [[Bergen]], Norway.<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=5605537|shipname=Barenfels |accessdate=19 July 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Baroda||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[File:Bombay-Docks-aftermath3.png|thumb|One of the ships damaged in the Bombay Explosion]][[Bombay Explosion (1944)|Bombay Explosion]]: The [[cargo liner]] wa