lted in the loss of many more ships.<ref name=FortKS>{{cite web |url=http://www.mariners-l.co.uk/FORT_K.html |title=Fort Ships K-S |publisher=Mariners |accessdate=5 January 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Graciosa||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Norway}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Bombay Explosion (1944)|Bombay Explosion]]: The cargo ship was severely damaged by the explosion of ''Fort Stikine'' ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}) and was declared a total loss. She was sold for scrap in July 1944.<ref name=Graciosa>{{cite web |url=http://www.warsailors.com/singleships/graciosa.html |title= D/S Graciosa |publisher=Warsailors |accessdate=13 January 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Generaal Van Der Heijden||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Netherlands|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Bombay Explosion (1944)|Bombay Explosion]]: The ship was lost as a result of the explosion of ''Fort Stikine'' ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}) at [[Bombay]], [[British India|India]].<ref name=\"Ships lost in the Bombay explosion\"/><ref name=KPM>{{cite web |url=http://www.theshipslist.com/ships/lines/kpm.shtml |title=Koninklijke Paketvaart Maatschappij 1888\u20131967 |publisher=The Ships List |accessdate=17 August 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Generaal Van Swiete||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Netherlands|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Bombay Explosion (1944)|Bombay Explosion]]: The ship was lost as a result of the explosion of ''Fort Stikine'' ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}) at [[Bombay]], [[British India|India]].<ref name=\"Ships lost in the Bombay explosion\"/><ref name=KPM/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Iran|1919|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Panama}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Bombay Explosion (1944)|Bombay Explosion]]: The cargo ship was severely damaged by the explosion of ''Fort Stikine'' ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}) and was declared a total loss.<ref name=Iran>{{cite web |url=http://www.warsailors.com/singleships/iran.html |title=D/S Iran |publisher=Warsailors |accessd