aur]], Norway by [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194404/><ref name=HomeV>{{cite web |url=http://www.warsailors.com/homefleet/shipsV.html |title=Norwegian Homefleet \u2013 WW II, Ships starting with V |publisher=Warsailors |accessdate=11 February 2012}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==15 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=15 April 1944 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 564||2}}  \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The Type C2 ''[[Marinef\u00e4hrprahm]]'' was sunk on this date.<ref name=\"MFP landing craft, Germany\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 569||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The Type C2M minelaying ''[[Marinef\u00e4hrprahm]]'' was sunk in the Black Sea by Soviet aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194404/><ref name=\"MFP landing craft, Germany\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Friedrichshafen|1943|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in the [[North Sea]] off [[Egersund]], Norway by {{HMS|Venturer|P68|6}} ({{navy|United Kingdom}}).<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=5615125|shipname=Friedrichshafen |accessdate=27 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese guard boat|Hakuo Maru||2}}  \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=The auxiliary guard boat was lost on this date.<ref name=\"ReferenceC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/japan/jap_esc_aux_pc.htm |title=Auxiliary Patrol and guard boats, Japan |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=22 May 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Rapel||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Chile}}\n|desc=The cargo ship struck a rock in the [[Guia Narrows]] and was beached ({{coord|58|45|S|74|25|W}}). She was declared a total loss.<ref name=Jordan447>{{cite book |title=The world's merchant fleets, 1939 |first=Roger |last=Jordan |publisher=Chatham publishing |location=London |year=1999 |page=447 |isbn=1 86176 023 X}}</re