ss than a minute, with 13 crewmen killed. The other 29 crewmen abandoned ship in a [[Lifeboat (shipboard)|lifeboat]], but only nine of them remained alive when the [[Steamship|steamer]] ''Ola'' ({{flag|Soviet Union}}) rescued them six days later. ''Pavlin Vinogradov''{{'}}s [[Sea captain|master]] did not survive.<ref name=alaskashipwrecksp>[https://alaskashipwreck.com/shipwrecks-a-z/alaska-shipwrecks-p/ alaskashipwreck.com Alaska Shipwrecks (P)]</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.shipsnostalgia.com/guides/Soviet_Merchant_Marine_Losses_in_WW2_%28Black_Sea%2C_Caspian_and_Pacific%29  |title=Soviet Marine Losses in WWII (Pacific Ocean)|publisher=Shipnostalgia.com |accessdate=13 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minelayer|Roland||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The auxiliary [[minelayer]] struck a mine and sank in the Baltic Sea.<ref name=seekrieg194403>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wlb-stuttgart.de/seekrieg/44-03.htm |title=Seekrieg 1944, M\u00e4rz |accessdate=3 August 2015 |last=Rohwer |first=J\u00fcrgen |authorlink=J\u00fcrgen Rohwer |author2=Gerhard H\u00fcmmelchen |work=W\u00fcrttembergische Landesbibliothek Stuttgart |publisher= |language=German }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese submarine chaser|Shonan Maru No. 7||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[submarine chaser]] was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Strait of Malacca]] by {{HMS|Sea Rover|P218|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-311||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC]] [[submarine]] was [[depth charge]]d and sunk in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] south west of Iceland ({{coord|52|09|N|19|07|W}}) by {{HMCS|Matane|K444|6}} and {{HMCS|Swansea|K328|6}} (both {{navy|Canada|1911}}) with the loss of all 51 crew.<ref name=U311>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/boats/u311.html |title=U-311 |publisher=Uboat |accessdat