ips/russia/ru_ls_tender1.htm |title= No. 11 class Landing Tender (1942), USSR |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=25 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German tug|O 22 S||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The [[tugboat|tug]] was sunk in an Allied air raid on [[Kiel]], [[Schleswig-Holstein]]. She was subsequently salvaged, repaired and returned to service.<ref name=Dunkirk>{{cite web |url=http://thamestugs.co.uk/DUNKIRK.php |title=Dunkirk |publisher=Thames Tugs |accessdate=18 October 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|R-208||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[R boat|Type R-151 minesweeper]] was sunk in the [[Danube]] at [[Linz]], Austria by a [[naval mine|mine]].<ref name=\"Warshipsww2.Eu\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German torpedo boat|T27||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The torpedo boat was shelled and damaged in the [[English Channel]] in a battle with {{HMS|Ashanti|F51|6}}, {{HMS|Black Prince|81|6}} (both {{navy|UK}}), {{HMCS|Haida|G63|6}} and {{HMCS|Huron|G24|6}} (both {{navy|Canada|1911}}). She was beached at [[Morlaix]], [[Manche]], France on 27 April. ''T 27'' was further damaged in an air attack on 3 May and was torpedoed and sunk by {{ship|HMMTB|673}} on 7 May.<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German torpedo boat|T29||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The torpedo boat was shelled and sunk in the English Channel by {{HMCS|Haida|G63|6}} ({{navy|Canada|1911}}) with the loss of 62 of her 135 crew. Survivors were rescued by Kriegsmarine ''[[Vorpostenboot]]e''.<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German torpedo boat|TA23||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Ciclone|torpedo boat|2}} was damaged by a mine off [[Capraia]], Italy ({{coord|43|02|N|10|12|E}}). Scuttled by ''TA29'' ({{navy|Nazi Germany}})