pth charge]]d, [[hedgehog (weapon)|hedgehogged]] and sunk in the [[Pacific Ocean]] south west of [[Chirikof Island]] ({{coord|55|09|57|N|155|40|00|W}}) by {{USS|Gilmore|DE-18|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}) with the loss of all 86 crew.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Itauri|1922|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk by aircraft south of Bod\u00f8, Norway.<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=5606020|shipname=Itauri |accessdate=29 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|J\u00e4\u00e4meri||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Finland}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship struck a [[naval mine|mine]] and sank in the [[Baltic Sea]] off [[Dar\u00df]], [[Mecklenburg-Vorpommern]], Germany.<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Kashiwa Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the Pacific Ocean north of [[Borneo]] by {{USS|Crevalle|SS-291|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|KT 3||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The ''[[Marinef\u00e4hrprahm]]'' was sunk in the North Sea west of [[Fugloy]], [[Faroe Islands]] by British aircraft. She was later salvaged and repaired.<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Lasbek||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk at [[Borkum]] by British aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Lotte Leonhardt|1937|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk by aircraft off Fuglo, south of Bod\u00f8, Norway.<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=5614750|shipname=Lotte Leonhardt |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Miike Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo liner was torpedoed an