libut|SS-232|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=Halibut/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|M 3668||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[minesweeper]], a  KFK-class [[naval drifter]], struck a mine and sank in the [[North Sea]] off [[Ostend]], [[West Flanders]], [[Belgium]].<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet motor torpedo boat|TK-332||2}}  \n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The G-5-class [[motor torpedo boat]] was shelled and sunk by German and Romanian surface ships in the [[black sea]].<ref name=\"G-5 class motor torpedo boat, USSR\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/russia/ru_cf_g5.htm |title=G-5 class motor torpedo boat, USSR |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=27 April 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Soviet Naval Losses Black Sea\">{{cite web |url=http://www.soviet-empire.com/ussr/viewtopic.php?f=149&t=53917&sid=0225559cd69b51f93f8b0cfbfab11342 |title=Soviet Naval Losses (Black Sea)|publisher=Sovietempire.com |accessdate=3 April 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-803||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type IX submarine|Type IXC/40]] [[submarine]] struck a mine and sank in the [[Baltic Sea]] off [[Swinem\u00fcnde]], [[Province of Pomerania (1815-1945)|Pomerania]], with the loss of nine of her 44 crew. Salvaged in August 1944 and cannibalized for parts.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German submarine chaser|UJ 104||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The auxiliary submarine chaser was torpedoed by {{ship|Soviet motor torpedo boat|TK-344||2}} ({{navy|Soviet Union}}) in the Black Sea, losing her stern. 17 crew were killed. She was towed to Sebastopol and was scuttled there on 10 May.<ref name=\"Soviet Naval Losses Black Sea\">{{cite web |url=http://www.soviet-empire.com/ussr/viewtopic.php?f=149&t=53917&sid=0225559cd69b51f93f8b0cfbfab11342 |title=Soviet Naval Losses (Black Sea